As part of the Future STEM Leaders Programme 2025 Cohort 1, an enlightening Introduction to Research Methodology Session was conducted on 30 October 2025. The session was hosted by Dr Habibur Rahman, Associate Professor at the University of Rajshahi, who guided participants through the fundamentals of research design, analytical thinking, and academic inquiry. Participants learned how to develop research questions, approach problems systematically, and apply critical thinking in scientific exploration. The session emphasized curiosity, precision, and ethical research practices essential for academic and professional growth. Organized under the SheSTEM banner, the discussion inspired young minds to embrace research-oriented learning. Through clear explanations and practical examples, participants gained confidence and motivation to pursue academic research, innovation, and evidence-based thinking in their future STEM journeys.